  "texts": [
    "A critical aspect of this new technology is the ability to interpret data of multiple types and origins 34, a recognised need in precision oncology 35.",
    "GMAI approaches can be repurposed to a wide range of tasks with limited manual human redesign, through drawing on knowledge of related problems 32.",
    "This integrated information can be used not only to interpret and to generate medical image and text data but also small molecules, nucleic acid sequences and proteins 36, including monoclonal antibodies 33.",
    "These technologies could be used in the near term to generate patient specific precision ATMPs, if the patient specific integration of rich molecular and clinical data is combined with existing molecular genetic techniques for rapid synthesis of proteins including receptors 18, 32, 37, 38.",
    "Regulatory approaches and resourcing are unlikely to keep pace with personalised therapy without a parallel paradigm shift."
  ],
